Jamany <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uedwinanytengayle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EdwinaNytengayle</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>RTA Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 178<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(1/8/01 5:21:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/TimesSquare/Labyrinth/1868/Ed.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Simple Question</span><hr size=1> It may be a simple question, Jamany; however, the answer is not so simple.<br>
<br>
A posting entity may invite who they wish to invite, within the guidelines of the rules (i.e. no more than 6 invites per guild/alliance).<br>
<br>
There is nothing that says an individual has a limit on the number of invites he/she can accept, nor is there anything that limits an individual to 1 raid per plane per cycle (whether that be month or whatever).  Example:  I have many friends in many guild/alliances.  It's entirely possible that I could go to the planes 2 or 3 times per week.<br>
<br>
You ask why is there not a restriction on individuals?  Rather than answering that straight up, lemme ask you this.  Just how do you propose to verify that over 2k people are only going to the planes once per cycle?<br>
<br>
You and I know that not everyone you know is from your own guild.  Through the travels throughout Norrath, you meet many people, some of whom become friends, some enemies, and others you just don't know at all.  One of the things discussed during the Big Debate was invites.  A posting entity is allowed to invite whomever they wish (within the rule of no more than 6 invites per guild/alliance).  In this manner, they can invite their friends along.<br>
<br>
If there was such a limitation as you question about, what makes you think that the posting entity would invite someone different?  They would most likely go without invites.  They do, after all, have a minimum of 40 people, which is more than enough to raid a plane (pre-SoV). <p><B><FONT FACE="Tahoma" COLOR="#ffffff">Edwina Nytengayle<BR>
