</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uelaundarnobillium.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elaundar Nobillium</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://home.stny.rr.com/drhager/sword.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>RTA Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 142<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(1/9/01 3:10:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What</span><hr size=1> Attention those who think the minimum 6 is not fair:<br>
<br>
I am in a guild of 12 that is allied with 2 other smallish guilds to get to the 40 minimum.  I was the one that pushed for the 6 minimum NOT the big guilds.<br>
<br>
The OLD rule was &quot;raids must have at least 2/3rds persent from the posting group.&quot;  This rule was DESTROYING the independant from getting a CHANCE at rare loot. Let me demonstrate:<br>
<br>
Guild A - has 40 members<br>
Guild B - has 40 members<br>
There are 20 independates that have good friends in both.<br>
<br>
Guild A needs armor for roughly HALF its guild (thats 20), so by the old rule they could invite up to 10 others TOTAL. They are great friends with guild B so they then invite 10 to their plane raid from that group.  Usually in return, guild B would do the same for guild A - basically giving BOTH guilds 2 plane dates per month.  Independants got screwed hard - they couldn't fill any of the precious spots, or the favor might not be returned to the guild.<br>
<br>
If acouple from guild A logged early, then all of a sudden you have as many from guild B as from guild A present.   Guess what - that is an alliance and both guilds are infact cheating to get extra time for their armor.  (This happened DAILY before - good guilds did it not just greedy ones.)<br>
<br>
Independants were NOT being invited... That was bad.<br>
<br>
The new rule makes the situation MUCH better:  Now guild A can go to the planes.  Their 20 members can invite ALL 20 indepentants they know as well as 6 from guild B.  They could invite 6 more from each of the posting guilds C, D, E, as well.  <br>
<br>
The 40 minimum was the flip side of this compromise.  The big guilds wanted this so as to PROVE that small guilds wouldn't be formed just to get into the planes more.  Small guilds and aliances wanted a number closer to 30 but we compromised when the big guilds areed to give us this minimum 6 rule instead of the 2/3rds rule.<br>
<br>
The reason that 6 from a posting group is allowed, is because friends in different guilds LIKE to play with each other.  YES some people are in the planes 5 days a week - but guess what -- THEY HAVE MANY FRIENDS! <br>
<br>
The 6 person invite was designed to HELP the smallest of guilds, and the independant player.  It was a compromise designed to help remove the multidate tricks AND allow unguilded to go to the planes.<br>
<br>
-------<br>
<br>
